info.senderName: NWS Duluth (Northeast Minnesota and Northern Wisconsin)
info.headline: Winter Storm Warning issued April 16 at 2:32PM CDT until April 17 at 7:00PM CDT by NWS Duluth
info.description: ...WINTER STORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 7 PM CDT MONDAY... * WHAT...Heavy mixed precipitation. Additional snow accumulations of 5 to 11 inches and ice accumulations of a light glaze. Winds gusting as high as 50 mph. * WHERE...Northern Cook and Lake and Southern Lake Counties. * WHEN...Until 7 PM CDT Monday. * IMPACTS...Travel will be very difficult. Blowing snow will significantly reduce visibility. The hazardous conditions could impact the morning or evening commute. Gusty winds could bring down tree branches. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Periods of blizzard conditions are possible especially closer to Lake Superior. Highest accumulations near the Gunflint Trail.
info.instruction: If you must travel, keep an extra flashlight, food, and water in your vehicle in case of an emergency. The latest road conditions can be obtained by calling 5 1 1. Road conditions can also be found at 511mn.org for Minnesota or 511wi.gov for Wisconsin.
